review_blob: Pretty nice Saison with a strong Blanche flavour, could have more smell tough, still very recommendable
A really nice Zwickel with a lot of yeast and a great head. Fresh taste, hints of citrus and grass, much better from tap than bottle. The best beer from Saarland, drinkable to the bitter end!

Quite an intense porter. Has a strong smoky and spicy smell. The body has a lot of chocolate and surprises with a lot of chili heat. Leaves you with a slight burnt bitterness and a nice chili afterglow. Definitely worth a taste!

Another uber bitter ale from Stone. Kind of a dark version of the ruination ale. Has a slight scent of raisins and bourbon. The body is quite bitter and grassy. Bitterness increases even further in the aftertaste and leaves an impression of ash on your tongue. Not really my cup of beer.
A fresh and accessible IPA with a fruity smell and body and moderate bitterness in the aftertaste. Head and appearance are rather disappointing though.
